# nested-writable-len baseline.
#
# Each entry below is a real bug candidate: a sanitiser line where the
# inner get_writable_struct() / get_writable_long_string() return value
# is assigned straight into a parent field without a NULL check, while
# a matching length / count field stays non-zero.  If the inner alloc
# returns NULL the kernel ioctl handler reads through a NULL pointer
# with a plausible length.
#
# Entries are grandfathered, not approved.  As each site is fixed (see
# ioctls/nvme.c for the canonical shape) its line MUST be removed from
# this file in the same commit -- the static check fails on stale
# baseline entries as well as new violators.  The baseline shrinks
# monotonically toward zero.
#
# Format: path:line  (relative to repo root)
